data.chText: 商品
data.enText: goods

data.chText: 生产；制造
data.enText: to make things to be sold, especially in large quantities

data.chText: 微芯片制造厂
data.enText: a factory that produces microchips

data.chText: 自然生产
data.enText: make naturally

data.chText: 生长；出产；繁育
data.enText: to grow or make sth as part of a natural process; to have a baby or young animal

data.chText: 这个地区出产全国50%以上的小麦。
data.enText: The region produces over 50% of the country's wheat.

data.chText: 我家的猫上周生小猫咪了。
data.enText: Our cat produced kittens last week.

data.chText: 她的任务就是生育王位继承人。
data.enText: Her duty was to produce an heir to the throne.

data.chText: 巧妙制作
data.enText: create with skill

data.chText: （运用技巧）制作，造出
data.enText: to create sth, especially when skill is needed

data.chText: 她利用几样剩下的东西烹制出一顿美味饭菜。
data.enText: She produced a delicious meal out of a few leftovers.

data.chText: 结果；效果
data.enText: result/effect

data.chText: 引起；导致；使产生
data.enText: to cause a particular result or effect

data.chText: 她给经理打了个电话便如愿以偿。
data.enText: A phone call to the manager produced the result she wanted.

data.chText: 这种药能使人产生兴奋的感觉。
data.enText: The drug produces a feeling of excitement.

data.chText: 展示；出示
data.enText: show/bring out

data.chText: 出示；展现；使出现
data.enText: to show sth or make sth appear from somewhere

data.chText: 他从口袋里掏出一封信来。
data.enText: He produced a letter from his pocket.

data.chText: 会上，财务总监出示了前一年的数字。
data.enText: At the meeting the finance director produced the figures for the previous year.

data.chText: 人
data.enText: person

data.chText: 栽培；培养
data.enText: if a town, country, etc. produces sb with a particular skill or quality, the person comes from that town, country, etc.

data.chText: 他是这个国家培养的最了不起的运动员。
data.enText: He is the greatest athlete this country has ever produced.

data.chText: 电影；戏剧
data.enText: movie/play

data.chText: 制作，拍摄（电影、戏剧等）；监督
data.enText: to be in charge of preparing a film/movie, play, etc. for the public to see

data.chText: 她拍了一部描写收养儿童的电视系列片。
data.enText: She produced a TV series about adopted children.

data.chText: 产品；（尤指）农产品
data.enText: things that have been made or grown, especially things connected with farming

data.chText: 农产品
data.enText: farm produce

data.chText: 这家商店专售当地的新鲜农产品。
data.enText: The shop sells only fresh local produce.

data.chText: 标签上写着“法国出产”。
data.enText: It says on the label ‘Produce of France’.

data.text: make ♦ create ♦ develop ♦ produce ♦ generate ♦ form

data.chText: 以上各词均含制造、使产生之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to make sth from parts or materials, or to cause sth to exist or happen.
make

data.chText: 指制造、做、组装、使产生：
data.enText: to create or prepare sth by combining materials or putting parts together; to cause sth to exist or happen

data.chText: 她自己做衣服。
data.enText: She makes her own clothes.

data.chText: 她给主持面试者留下了很好的印象。
data.enText: She made a good impression on the interviewer.
create

data.chText: 指创造、创作、创建：
data.enText: to make sth exist or happen, especially sth new that did not exist before

data.chText: 科学家对宇宙是怎样形成的有分歧。
data.enText: Scientists disagree about how the universe was created.

data.chText: 用make还是create？
make较通用，较常用以指物质的东西，如制造桌子、做衣服、做蛋糕通常用make，但创造就业机会/财富用create。要强调某物品或实体事物是原创的或不同寻常，也可用create：
data.enText: Make is a more general word and is more often used for physical things: you would usually make a table/dress/cake but create jobs/wealth . You can use create for sth physical in order to emphasize how original or unusual the object is.

data.chText: 品尝一下这道新菜吧，是我们厨师长首创的。
data.enText: Try this new dish, created by our head chef.
make or create?
develop

data.chText: （尤用于商务语境）开发，研制（产品）：
data.enText: (used especially in business contexts) to think of and produce a new product

data.chText: 开发新软件
data.enText: to develop new software
produce

data.chText: 指生产、制造（商品）；（运用技巧）制作、造出：
data.enText: to make things to be sold; to create sth using skill

data.chText: 微芯片制造厂
data.enText: a factory that produces microchips
generate

data.chText: 指创造、产生（电、财富或主意）：
data.enText: to produce or create sth, especially power, money or ideas

data.chText: 发电
data.enText: to generate electricity

data.chText: 集思广益是出主意的好办法。
data.enText: Brainstorming is a good way of generating ideas.
form

data.chText: 指制作、组成、制成：
data.enText: [often passive] to make sth from sth else; to make sth into sth else

data.chText: 重新排列字母，组成另一单词。
data.enText: Rearrange the letters to form a new word.

data.chText: 这根链条由136个链节组成。
data.enText: The chain is formed from 136 links.
to make/create/develop/produce/generate/form sth from/out of sth
to make/form sth into sth
to make/produce wine
to create/develop a new product
to create/produce/generate income/profits/wealth
to produce/generate electricity/heat/power

data.text: product ♦ goods ♦ commodity ♦ merchandise ♦ produce ♦ wares

data.chText: 以上各词均指产品、商品。
data.enText: These are all words for things that are produced to be sold.
product

data.chText: 指制造或种植的产品：
data.enText: a thing that is produced or grown, usually to be sold

data.chText: 创造／开发／推出新产品
data.enText: to create/develop/launch a new product
goods

data.chText: 指商品、货品：
data.enText: things that are produced to be sold

data.chText: 棉织／皮革商品
data.enText: cotton/leather goods

data.chText: 电器商品
data.enText: electrical goods
commodity

data.chText: 尤指国家间贸易的商品：
data.enText: ( economics ) a product or raw material that can be bought and sold, especially between countries

data.chText: 稻米、面粉和其他基本商品
data.enText: rice, flour and other basic commodities
merchandise

data.chText: 指商品、货品、相关商品、指定商品：
data.enText: [U] goods that are bought or sold; things that you can buy that are connected with or advertise a particular event or organization

data.chText: 奥林匹克运动会官方指定商品
data.enText: official Olympic merchandise

data.chText: 用goods还是merchandise？
强调商品制作的原料或用途用goods：
data.enText: Choose goods if the emphasis is on what the product is made of or what it is for.

data.chText: 皮革商品；家庭用品
data.enText: leather/household goods

data.chText: 如果不太强调商品本身，而更强调品牌或买卖用merchandise。
data.enText: Choose merchandise if the emphasis is less on the product itself and more on its brand or the fact of buying/selling it.
goods or merchandise?
produce

data.chText: 尤指农产品，也包括其他种植或制造的产品：
data.enText: [U] things that have been grown or made, especially things connected with farming

data.chText: 我们只售当地的新鲜农产品。
data.enText: We sell only fresh local produce.
wares

data.chText: 尤指小商贩在大街上或市场里出售的物品：
data.enText: things that sb is selling, especially in the street or at a market

data.chText: 摊售货品的街头小贩
data.enText: street traders displaying their wares

data.chText: wares在过去指小贩走乡串镇出售的物品，在现代社会可指商贩兜售的不太值钱的商品。
data.enText: Wares is used about people in the past who travelled from town to town selling things; when used in a modern context it can suggest that sb is trying to persuade people to buy sth that has not much value.
to sell/market/export a product/goods/a commodity/merchandise/produce/your wares
to buy/purchase a product/goods/a commodity/merchandise/produce/sb's wares
household products/goods/commodities/wares
consumer/industrial products/goods/commodities
dairy/farm products/produce
luxury products/goods/commodities
a range of products/goods/commodities/merchandise/wares

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 向前 + duce 引导；带来 → 向前产出 → 生产

ex.chText: 那个超市里出售各种各样的农产品。
ex.enText: Various kinds of agricultural products are sold in that supermarket.
Where are the finished products assembled?

synonyms.bx: 指种植的物产或工厂里大批量制造的产品，通常用于出售。

ex.chText: 下一步是开发庞大的消费品市场。
ex.enText: The next step is to tap the large market for consumer goods.

ex.chText: 皮革类制品在那个国家很受欢迎。
ex.enText: Leather goods are very popular in that country.

synonyms.bx: 只用复数形式，泛指用于出售的货品。

ex.chText: 一系列正版的史努比商品在游客中心出售。
ex.enText: A range of official Snoopy merchandise is on sale in the visitors' centre.

ex.chText: 货到之后他们检查过吗？
ex.enText: Did they inspect the merchandise after its arrival?

synonyms.bx: 不可数名词，指供买卖的货物。

ex.chText: 新鲜的本地农产品通常物美价廉。
ex.enText: Fresh local produce is usually cheap and delicious.

synonyms.bx: 不可数名词，指生产出来用于出售的农产品。

tr: fresh fruits and vegetable grown for the market
come to have or undergo a change of (physical features and attributes)
example: He grew a beard
The patient developed abdominal pains
I got funny spots all over my body
Well-developed breasts

tr: create or manufacture a man-made product
example: We produce more cars than we can sell
The company has been making toys for two centuries

tr: cultivate by growing, often involving improvements by means of agricultural techniques
example: The Bordeaux region produces great red wines
They produce good ham in Parma
We grow wheat here
We raise hogs here
The tree would not produce fruit

tr: cause to happen, occur or exist
example: This procedure produces a curious effect
The new law gave rise to many complaints
These chemicals produce a noxious vapor
the new President must bring about a change in the health care system
The proud father produced many pictures of his baby
The accused brought forth a letter in court that he claims exonerates him

tr: bring onto the market or release
example: produce a movie
bring out a book
produce a new play

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /prə'djuːs, am -'duːs/. The noun is pronounced /'prɒdjuːs, am -duːs/ and is hyphenated prod|uce. 动词读作 /prə'djuːs, 美 -'duːs/。名词读作 /'prɒdjuːs, 美 -duːs/，分音节形式为 prod|uce。

value.def: To produce something means to cause it to happen.

example.ex: The drug is known to produce side-effects in women...
example.tran: 据悉，这种药会对女性产生副作用。

example.ex: Talks aimed at producing a new world trade treaty have been under way for six years.
example.tran: 旨在制定出一个新的世界贸易条约的谈判已经进行了6年。

value.def: If you produce something, you make or create it.

example.ex: The company produced circuitry for communications systems...
example.tran: 该公司为通信系统生产电路。

example.ex: I'm quite pleased that we do have the capacity to produce that much food.
example.tran: 我很高兴我们确实有能力生产这么多粮食。

value.def: When things or people produce something, it comes from them or slowly forms from them, especially as the result of a biological or chemical process.

example.ex: These plants are then pollinated and allowed to mature and produce seed.
example.tran: 然后，这些植物就被授粉，从而成熟结籽。

example.ex: ...gases produced by burning coal and oil.
example.tran: 煤和油燃烧时产生的气体

value.def: If you produce evidence or an argument, you show it or explain it to people in order to make them agree with you.

example.ex: They challenged him to produce evidence to support his allegations...
example.tran: 他们要他拿出证据证明自己的主张。

example.ex: Scientists have produced powerful arguments against his ideas.
example.tran: 科学家们提出了有力论据反驳他的观点。

value.def: If you produce an object from somewhere, you show it or bring it out so that it can be seen.

example.ex: To hire a car you must produce a passport and a current driving licence...
example.tran: 租车必须出示护照和有效驾驶执照。

example.ex: She produced the knife during arguments with her friends.
example.tran: 在和朋友争吵的时候，她掏出了刀。

value.def: If someone produces something such as a film, a magazine, or a CD, they organize it and decide how it should be done.

example.ex: He has produced his own sports magazine called Yes Sport...
example.tran: 他推出了自己的体育杂志，叫做《是的，体育》。

example.ex: He produced 'A Chorus Line', Broadway's longest running show.
example.tran: 他制作推出了《歌舞线上》这一百老汇经久不衰的剧目。

value.tran: 上演（戏剧）；制作（电影、电视节目）；灌制（唱片）

value.def: Produce is food or other things that are grown in large quantities to be sold.

example.ex: We manage to get most of our produce in Britain...
example.tran: 我们设法在英国搞到我们所需的大部分农产品。

example.ex: Winter produce will cost more for the next few weeks.
example.tran: 在未来几周，冬季农产品会更贵。
